  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "After a while, then my-- I was transferred to the city, to my parents, who had then-- there was a family meeting and my grandparents, who had been living with my mother's sister, had now decided that they were going to live with us.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And the sister and her husband moved out to New Jersey, and my parents and my grandparents took an apartment in Astoria, New York, and this is where we were going to continue living.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very, very little.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When my father came out of the concentration camp, although raised in an orthodox fashion, he said there was no God and never referred to God again in all of our traveling.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When we got to New York, my mother's family was not observant at all, and so there was no emphasis on religion in the house.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "However, my own outlook-- I suppose in adult years you would call it philosophy-- but my own outlook on life was such that I felt very grateful to God for having gotten me to the point where we were together and in good health.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I always, from then on and still do, feel very strongly that I survived in order to-- to live a Jewish life, to raise children in the Jewish faith, and thus be part of procreation and populating a small corner of the world with Jewish adults and children, that that was somewhat of a mission.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I also felt it was an obligation to those of my family who perished, both my mother-- both my grandmother at the age of 89 and my aunt, Clementine, and her husband were deported.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My aunt and uncle went to [INAUDIBLE], which is in Poland, to a camp, and were lost, annihilated, there.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
